Nanocomposites were also synthesized using already established lab protocol [13,30]. Briefly, the production of a nanocomposite was carried out within a two-neck round bottom flask under inert conditions. The reaction setup was mounted onto a magnetic stirrer and DMAEMA was introduced, subsequently followed by a gradual addition of AAc. The mixture was then continuously stirred on an ice bath for a duration of 10 min. The monomer mixture was subjected to continuous stirring for a duration of 15–20 min, following which water containing varying concentrations of sonicated CQDs (Table 1
                        ), APS, and TEMED were introduced. Subsequently, the composition that was prepared was introduced into the desired molds, securely enclosed, and subsequently immersed in a water bath maintained at a temperature of 40 ± 2 °C for a duration of 24 h. After the process of polymerization was finished (Scheme 1
                        ), the resultant samples were removed from the molds and subjected to a 2–3 day washing procedure with distilled water to eliminate any unreacted monomers. The nanocomposites were dried and subsequently preserved for future utilization.
